correctness.rationale: The extraction contains numerous fabricated or incorrect values and several schema issues, with weak traceability to the article. Key problems: (1) Schema violations/placeholder misuse: plasmaPower is null (type object expected, and PEALD was not used), and many required fields are filled with non-informative placeholders ('Not Found') rather than factual values (e.g., carrierGas, purgingGas, reactor details, deliveryMethod), violating the factual alignment requirement. (2) Invented process parameters: dosingTime, purgeTime, flowRates, saturation=False, nucleationPeriod=10 cycles, growthPerCycle=0.133 Å, supercycleDesign entries, uniformity (5%), conformality (aspect ratio 10) are not reported in the paper. The GPC×cycles (0.133 Å × 1500 ≈ 20 nm) is inconsistent with the stated 200 nm film thickness. (3) Pressure is set to 5 mmHg without support; the paper only states 'a few mbar' (no numeric value; 5 mmHg ≈ 6.7 mbar is an invented number). (4) Optical properties are largely fabricated: refractive index and absorption coefficient not reported; band gap trend is discussed but no explicit numeric value is given, yet 3.3 eV is inserted. (5) Electrical properties have serious unit/value errors: resistivity should be 1.7×10^-3 Ω·cm for the 200 °C film (Table 1), i.e., 1.7×10^-5 Ω·m, but 0.0017 Ω·m is given (100× too high). Carrier density 1.3×10^20 cm^-3 is reported; extraction uses 1.3e20 with unit C-PER-M3 and no cm→m conversion (should be 1.3×10^26 m^-3 with unit PER-M3 per schema). Mobility 28.7 cm^2/Vs is correct. (6) Film composition misinterpretation: the article reports an O/Zn atomic ratio of 0.86 (Zn=1) from EDX; the extraction lists elementalConcentration as 86% which is not supported. (7) Film density (5.6 g/dm^3) is fabricated and unit choice implies an unphysical density; no density was reported. (8) DeviceProperties (TFT metrics) are entirely fabricated; the article did not fabricate devices. Correct items include: ALD of ZnO using DEZn and deionized water, substrate (glass), temperature 200 °C, film thickness ~200 nm, mobility 28.7 cm^2/Vs, roughness 1.51 nm, polycrystalline phase, and O/Zn=1:0.86 ratio. To correct: fix resistivity to 1.7e-5 Ω·m; convert carrier density to 1.3e26 m^-3 with unit PER-M3; remove or mark as not reported (and avoid guessing) pressure value, GPC, dosing/purge/flows, saturation, nucleationPeriod, uniformity, conformality, optical index/absorption/band gap numeric, film density, and all device metrics; correct film composition reporting to the atomic ratio provided.

completeness.rationale: Very poor completeness and factual alignment. (1) Multiple processes missing: the article reports four ZnO ALD depositions at 120, 160, 200, and 240 °C (all ~200 nm films with distinct electrical/compositional data), but only a single process (200 °C) is extracted. Each temperature condition should be represented as a separate process with the corresponding properties from Table 1 and Table 2. (2) Numerous values are fabricated or not traceable: dosing times, purge times, flow rates, nucleation period, saturation flag, supercycle design, refractive index, absorption coefficient, uniformity (%), conformality (aspect ratio), film density (and XRR method), and all deviceProperties (TFT metrics) are not reported in the article. (3) Several factual/units errors: resistivity reported as 0.0017 Ω·m (should be 1.7×10⁻⁵ Ω·m converted from 1.7×10⁻³ Ω·cm), carrier density given as 1.3×10²⁰ with unit C·m⁻³ (should be number density 1.3×10²⁶ m⁻³ with unit PER-M3), pressure entered as 5 mmHg while the paper only says “a few mbar” (unit mismatch and ungrounded numeric), growth-per-cycle 0.133 Å is off by ~10× and not supported; number of cycles 1500 conflicts with the 200 nm films (the paper says different cycles were used to reach 200 nm). (4) Schema issues/traceability: plasmaPower is null (violates schema type), carrierGas and purgingGas are filled with “Not Found” placeholders (not traceable); reactor name/manufacturer likewise. (5) Substrate handling incomplete: both glass and Si were used (e.g., thickness on Si, cross-sections on Si), but only glass is captured. Properties to add/review: add three more processes (120, 160, 240 °C) with correct temperature, substrate(s), film thickness, resistivity, mobility, carrier density, and O/Zn atomic ratio; correct units/conversions for resistivity and carrier density; correct or remove unreported fields (dosing/purge/flows/film density/uniformity/conformality/device metrics) to maintain traceability; fix pressure to a traceable value or leave unspecified; correct GPC/number of cycles if supported by the article; avoid nulls and placeholders that are not grounded in the text.
